                            <comment id="12581811" author="jorgenlo" created="Tue, 25 Mar 2008 07:38:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch 1a shuts down the database after failing a credential check for the startSlave command. This will only happen if the database has not been booted already due to EmbedConnnection lines 277-282:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            if (isStartSlaveBoot) {&lt;br/&gt;
                if (database != null) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                    throw StandardException.newException(
                        SQLState.CANNOT_START_SLAVE_ALREADY_BOOTED,
                        getTR().getDBName());
                }

&lt;p&gt;With the patch, the repro works as expected. All tests passed except testStartStopManagementFromApplication which also fails tinderbox. Requesting review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12582273" author="oysteing" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2008 12:51:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am also not quite sure what is the best error to get in the case&lt;br/&gt;
that you try start a slave on a already booted database with invalid&lt;br/&gt;
credentials.  Should a a user that is not authorized to boot the&lt;br/&gt;
database, be able to learn whether it is booted or not through a&lt;br/&gt;
startSlave command?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12582274" author="oysteing" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2008 12:52:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you plan to add any test cases for this issue to the replication test suite?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12582676" author="jorgenlo" created="Thu, 27 Mar 2008 15:02:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reviewing the patch. Patch 1b addresses the issue that unauthorized users should not get to know if a database has been booted or not. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All tests passed. Requesting review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12582679" author="jorgenlo" created="Thu, 27 Mar 2008 15:04:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Do you plan to add any test cases for this issue to the replication test suite?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, but a security manager is required for that. Currently, the replication test framework does not support the security manager. I added this issue to the list of missing regression tests on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3403&quot; title=&quot;Add replication regression tests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3403&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3403&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12583059" author="oysteing" created="Fri, 28 Mar 2008 15:09:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, J&#248;rgen. Committed patch derby-3549-1b.diff at revision 642219.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12584495" author="oysteing" created="Wed, 2 Apr 2008 11:13:08 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged to 10.4 branch at revision 643828.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
